# SecondBrain

Local-first, Markdown-centered second brain. Created by the SecondBrain
installer v{{VERSION}} on {{DATE}}.

```text
Original documents are evidence.        -> 10-originals/
Converted Markdown is retrieval substrate. -> 20-converted/
Curated Markdown is trusted knowledge.  -> 30-curated/
Basic Memory is structured agent memory. -> 40-agent-memory/
QMD is lookup.                           -> 70-scripts/search/
MCP is the agent interface.              -> 70-scripts/mcp/
Git is the temporal and versioning backbone.
Obsidian is the human interface.
```

## Layout

| Folder | Purpose | Trust |
|---|---|---|
| `00-inbox/` | Drop zone; files here get ingested and converted | transient |
| `10-originals/` | Canonical source artifacts — never modified | evidence |
| `20-converted/` | MarkItDown projections of originals | source-derived, unreviewed |
| `30-curated/` | Human-reviewed knowledge, decisions, summaries | trusted |
| `40-agent-memory/` | Agent-written observations and relations | unreviewed until promoted |
| `50-context-packs/` | Compact task-specific bundles for agents | generated |
| `60-index-config/` | Schemas, collections, manifests, install state | config |
| `70-scripts/` | Conversion, search, context, maintenance, MCP | tooling |
| `80-logs/` | Conversion / indexing / agent-access logs | disposable |
| `90-archive/` | Cold storage | archived |

## Manual lookup (you)

Open this folder in Obsidian (Open folder as vault). Search in this order:
`30-curated/decisions` → `30-curated/summaries` → `30-curated/concepts` →
`40-agent-memory/project-memory` → `20-converted` → `10-originals`.
Promote anything useful into `30-curated/` and link it back to its sources.

## Agentic lookup (Claude Code, Codex, …)

Agents get scoped tools via the `second-brain` MCP server — staged retrieval
over curated decisions first, raw conversions last, plus bounded memory
writes into `40-agent-memory/`. Agents do not crawl the vault.

## Everyday commands

```bash
# Drop files into 00-inbox/raw-drops, then:
70-scripts/convert/convert_new_documents.sh

# Search from the command line:
70-scripts/search/search_curated.sh --query "identity resolution"
70-scripts/search/search_decisions.sh --query "architecture" --max-results 5

# Build an agent context pack:
70-scripts/context/build_context_pack.py --topic "identity-resolution" --project introhive

# Housekeeping:
70-scripts/maintenance/validate_frontmatter.py
70-scripts/maintenance/find_unreviewed_conversions.py
```

## Rules the tooling enforces

- Originals are never modified or overwritten; duplicates are detected by checksum.
- Converted Markdown is regenerable and carries `review_status: unreviewed`
  frontmatter until a human reviews it.
- Agents write only to `40-agent-memory/` and `50-context-packs/`.
- Nothing pushes to a remote or deletes notes without a human doing it.
